Finance & Accounting Specialist - SingaporePosted 11 hours agoExperienceEntry levelJob functionFinanceEmployment typeFull-timeIndustryDesignJob ID13691157This is a preview of the Finance & Accounting Specialist job at IDEO. To view the full job listing, join LinkedIn - its free!Join LinkedIn - its free!About this jobJob descriptionIDEO, a global innovation and design consultancy is looking for a Finance & Accounting Specialist to join our team in our Singapore office. This position reports directly to the Co-Location Head, dotted line to Asia accounting lead. Our ideal candidate has high levels of empathy, self-motivation, strong customer service orientation and has an ability to thrive in a non-rule based, innovation and design led culture.   We are a highly networked organization that functions through relationships, trust and collaboration. The successful candidate is someone with 2-3 years of experience in billing, credit and collections role and accounts payable.  Experience in a media, creative or professional service firm would be a plus.Desired Skills and ExperienceAccounts Payable The accountant will receive and verify vendor invoices, make payment to ensure they follow proper policies and procedures. Must be strong with data entry and problem solving while batching invoices using Great Plains accounting system. Cash & Bank reconciliation. Local corporate credit card maintenance, monthly statement reconciliation and ensure book entry correct and in time. Correspond with vendors/team members, respond to inquiries and resolve billing and payment issues   Accounts Receivable  Work closely with the Business Operations Team across a portfolio of clients, to ensure invoicing and collection efforts are performed in accordance with signed contracts and change orders Ensure client account balances are properly reconciled with internal accounting systems. Deliver supplemental billing data per contractual terms Prepare weekly AR aging, Unbilled Project Expense and Labor reports and take appropriate follow up actions Actively manage AR aging and drive collection activities on past due accounts.   Month end Close & others Assist month-end & audit processes and perform other ad-hoc accounting duties as required Participate in on-going process improvement around A/R and other Finance initiatives across the firm Prepare analysis of accounts and any other responsibilities assigned   Education, Experience and Skills: B.S. in Accounting or Finance or related field required. Strong Excel Skill and familiarity with automated project billing systems and Great Plains is highly desirable Minimum 2 year's Accounting experience Familiar with Singapore local accounting regulation Good command of English, both oral/written Exceptional interpersonal skills and possess the ability to communicate clearly with all levels of personnel from staff level to senior management and with clients, displaying tact and diplomacy and a strong orientation towards customer-service Outstanding organizational, prioritization and multitasking skills Ability to keep commitments and maintain a high degree of attention to detailAbout this companyIDEOIDEO* has roots dating back to 1978. Today, IDEO is an award-winning global design and innovation consultancy. We create positive impact through design by taking a human-centered approach to helping organizations in the public and private sectors innovate, grow, and bring to market new ideas. + We partner with leaders and change agents to identify new market opportunities, add value, and solve meaningful problems. + We design and launch innovative products, services, ventures, and brands by combining business acumen with human-centered market insights. + We help organizations to build the capabilities required to sustain innovation. *Pronounced “EYE-dee-oh” IDEOが高く評価するのは、前向きに人と協力でき、責任感が強く、さまざまな考え方を受け入れ、口で言うよりもまず行動し、失敗から学ぶことができ、自分以外の人の成功のために一所懸命になれる人材です。IDEOの楽しい職場は、熱意と自主性があり、細かいところにも気を配れる柔軟なチームプレイヤーにぴったりです。優れた対人能力と判断力があり、覚えが速く、スマートに働き、全力で遊べる人をお待ちしています。 斬新な視点とふさわしいスキルを持ち、IDEOの価値観に共感してもらえる方は、ぜひ私たちのスタジオで力を発揮してみてください。ご応募をお待ちしています。
